title: For Sale:  RWS/Diana 52 (48, 52, 54) Pellet Gun Rifle With Scope No Longer Made
postcontent: For sale is a used but in great shape RWS model 52. This one hails from the Cold War era, as evidenced by the "made in west germany" stamp on the side and DIANA logo on the receiver. These are no longer available and the build quality on the old DIANA rifles must be felt to be believed. I purchased this one used from B and B Supply in south Minneapolis and have tuned and rebuilt the piston with new grease and a new piston seals. This process involves mirror polishing the inside of the piston cylinder and reassembling the action with new grease, seals, etc. This gives the gun a very smooth and consistent power stroke. Additionally, I have installed a lighter weight Beeman muzzle brake (which required modification to outer barrel sleeve for fit), added a heavy duty scope base that can withstand the recoil of the spring piston and mounted a 3-9x 50 red/green illuminated reticle mil-dot scope. 48/52s have an adjustable trigger and an automatic tang mounted safety. Checkered Monte Carlo stock. Please contact me with any questions, rifle will sell with everything pictured, minus case. Will remove scope/base to sell separately if you already have one in mind, otherwise would like to sell as package.  Thanks!
